content: I have been looking at new/different launchers for over a week now on my Acer A200. I usually use Apex on everything and always use Apex on my phone. However, I wanted to try out a lot of different launchers and see if there was anything out there that I liked enough to use. I have been through 10-15 different launchers before finally finding Lucid Launcher. I really like this Launcher on my Acer A200 10.1" tablet. So far the only thing I noticed that was strange was that when sending apps to the home screen it stacks them on top of one another when I do a lot of them. This launcher is faster than Nova Pro & very customizable. If you love Nova (Pro) or Zeam, you'll love Lucid Launcher Pro. Try the free version out. It's the most affordable Pro Launcher out there at $2.  The first thing to get past is it conforms to Android Application Designs regarding menus & swipe actions. That means *no persistent icon bar*. There's a slideout Favorites available, but if you use just 2 or 3 screens, it's far easier to put the Phone icon on every screen - it would have been there anyway but on bar.   Take a personal challenge. Use the free version, give it a week. If you have multiple devices, put it on all them. You need complete immersion to try it out as the "schism" is too great between launchers. The confusion will make you abandon the challenge. You are effectively breaking a bad habit.  Then after the week (or better two) challenge, try out your old launcher. It will feel slow, bloated & awkward. You'll then realize, you'll need to go Pro for $2.  Oh, BTW, for folks who are still using Nova Pro - your launcher is still constantly pinging the Internet for stuff. Install NoRoot Firewall by Grey Shirts. You'll see.

This launcher was made from scratch and we have to implement every feature one by one so it does take time but were releasing weekly updates that add these features. Thanks.

content: Great for multitasking. One thing that would be nice is infinite scroll, wallpaper and working icon themes.

userName: John Nada Theming. Home Screen Design
content: Updates are great and seem to come quickly, at least since I've started using. Good job!

My widgets will get thrown around by accidentally long pressing, make an option to lock the desktop and I'll reward you will all your stars. Update: well I feel like a fool, it was right in plain sight. As promised, here are your stars.
replyContent: Hi, There is an option to lock the desktop, simply tap on the 3 dots menu if you have the search-actionbar enabled and click lock desktop. If you have search-actionbar disabled simply hold on a blank space and click lock desktop. Thanks.

3 stars for now until bugs get fixed, and at the moment I can't even set it as my launcher, worked for a few minutes then crashed.
replyContent: Hi. You should test out the latest version. Many bugs have been fixed. Thanks!

content: Just missing some basic things like folders. Love the concept. Widgets come in at full page size though. Keep up the good work.

Best launcher on play store. Slide technique is fantastic and browser is better than chrome and as good as dolphin. Developer responds promptly, couldn't ask for better. Works with many different icon packs that makes it even better. Outstanding support ,best that I've came across with any developer on play store. Give it a try , it will be the best money you spend on play store.

Still beta so few bugs here and there(crash when trying to remove some widgets) but otherwise it works well. Like the vertical scrolling homescreens. Like with many other launchers, I wish it had the same app sorting as Smart launcher.  Having all apps in the same list is a pain.
Its awesome!

I've been following this developer since he launched this app, and I've been very, very pleased with the fast-acting dedication and hard work he has put into his launcher. As a power user, I consistently root my phones and my tablet and tweak every minute thing to my liking. Ultimately though, it is the launcher that is one's home on Android, and I'm happy to say, Lucid is mine. What is most impressive to me is his engagement with the community on G+.  Keep it up, man. You're doing fantastic.
This isn't just "another launcher, yawn." This is an innovative product from a talented and responsive Dev who cares about his user community. Spend a couple dollars and stop being so tight.
This is great and only gets better
Big fan of this launcher.. Pro version well worth it to help support this unique take on the user interface. I appreciate your efforts.

I love this launcher, and with the release of Pro it has really grown up. The $2 is worth every penny as it unlocks some nice tools/settings that allow you just a little more control over your experience. I have had no problems on my N5.

Finally, a launcher done just right. Not too many features, not too less features. Developers are awesome as well. Very quick to response. Must follow their G+ page. Fastest way to get answers and request features.
